{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-b5495c62bd27e0de", "type": "tool_result", "content": "{\"arxiv_id\": \"2604.10708\", \"title\": \"Audio-Omni: Extending Multi-modal Understanding to Versatile Audio Generation and Editing\", \"authors\": [\"Zeyue Tian\", \"Binxin Yang\", \"Zhaoyang Liu\", \"Jiexuan Zhang\", \"Ruibin Yuan\", \"Hubery Yin\", \"Qifeng Chen\", \"Chen Li\", \"Jing Lv\", \"Wei Xue\", \"Yike Guo\"], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.AI\", \"cs.CV\", \"cs.MM\"], \"topic\": \"tts_vc\", \"tags\": [\"LALM\", \"LALM/\\u97f3\\u9891\\u6807\\u8bb0-\\u878d\\u5408\", \"TTS\", \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u8bed\\u97f3\\u7f16\\u8f91\"], \"contributions\": [\"We propose Audio-Omni, the first unified framework for audio understanding, generation, and editing across general sound, music, and speech, featuring a decoupled architecture that bridges a frozen MLLM with a trainable DiT via a hybrid conditioning mechanism.\", \"We introduce AudioEdit, a large-scale, high-quality dataset comprising over one million curated instruction-guided audio editing pairs constructed through a hybrid pipeline of real-world data mining and programmatic synthesis.\", \"Extensive experiments demonstrate that Audio-Omni outperforms prior unified models and achieves competitive or superior results compared to specialized expert models across a broad range of tasks.\", \"Audio-Omni exhibits remarkable inherited capabilities from the frozen MLLM, such as knowledge-augmented generation and zero-shot cross-lingual control, highlighting a path toward intelligent and versatile generative audio systems.\"], \"citations\": [{\"paper_id\": \"2406.03644\", \"title\": \"Audio Flamingo3\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized understanding model compared against in Table 1\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen2.5-Omni-3B\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Pretrained and frozen MLLM used as the core understanding module and feature extractor\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Gemini 2.5 Pro\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"MLLM used for category recognition of source audio in VGGSound\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SAM-Audio\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Model deployed for source separation based on recognized categories\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CLAP\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used for semantic alignment filtering in real data branch and style transfer construction\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"ZETA\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Used to convert target audio to new style while preserving temporal structure and pitch\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Scaper\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Toolkit used for programmatic soundscape generation in the synthetic data branch\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VGGSound\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Real-world audio dataset used as input for the AudioEdit dataset construction engine\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"ESC-50\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Foreground sound dataset used for synthetic data generation in AudioEdit\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioCaps\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Background audio dataset used for synthetic data generation in AudioEdit and as T2A generation benchmark\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Synchformer\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Pretrained model used to extract video synchronization features at 25fps\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"ConvNeXtV2\", \"cite_type\": \"supported_by\", \"context\": \"Architecture used for the transcription encoder (4 blocks) in the generation module\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MMSU\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Understanding benchmark with 47 spoken language tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MMAU\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Understanding benchmark across 27 reasoning skills in sound/music/speech\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Musicaps\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Text-to-music (T2M) generation benchmark\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"V2M-bench\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Video-to-music (V2M) generation benchmark\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Seed-TTS en\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Text-to-speech (TTS) generation benchmark\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioEdit\", \"cite_type\": \"eval_by\", \"context\": \"Constructed audio editing dataset with 2000 test samples used for evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Qwen2-Audio-Instruct\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized understanding model evaluated on MMSU and MMAU benchmarks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Tango2\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized generation model compared against in generation tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MMAudio\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized generation model compared against in generation tasks and human V2A evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Stable-Audio-Open\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized generation model compared against in generation tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MusicGen\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized generation model compared against in generation tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VATT\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized generation model compared against in generation tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"AudioX\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized generation model compared against in generation tasks and human V2A evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VidMuse\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized generation model compared against in generation tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"F5-TTS\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized generation model compared against in generation tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MaskGCT\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized generation model compared against in generation tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CosyVoice3\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized generation model compared against in generation tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"SDEdit\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized editing model compared against in editing tasks and human evaluation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MMEDIT\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized editing model compared against in editing tasks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Ming-Omni\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Unified model compared against on understanding and generation benchmarks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"Unified-IO2\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Unified model compared against on understanding and generation benchmarks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"MuMuLLaMA\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Unified model compared against on understanding and generation benchmarks\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"T5\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized single-modal encoder compared against MLLM unified encoder in ablation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"CLIP\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized single-modal encoder compared against MLLM unified encoder in ablation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}, {\"paper_id\": \"\", \"title\": \"VideoMAE\", \"cite_type\": \"compared_with\", \"context\": \"Specialized single-modal encoder compared against MLLM unified encoder in ablation\", \"bib_key\": \"\", \"source\": \"llm\"}], \"code_url\": \"\", \"abstract\": \"Recent progress in multimodal models has spurred rapid advances in audio understanding, generation, and editing. However, these capabilities are typically addressed by specialized models, leaving the development of a truly unified framework that can seamlessly integrate all three tasks underexplored. While some pioneering works have explored unifying audio understanding and generation, they often remain confined to specific domains. To address this, we introduce Audio-Omni, the first end-to-end framework to unify generation and editing across general sound, music, and speech domains, with integrated multi-modal understanding capabilities. Our architecture synergizes a frozen Multimodal Large Language Model for high-level reasoning with a trainable Diffusion Transformer for high-fidelity synthesis. To overcome the critical data scarcity in audio editing, we construct AudioEdit, a new large-scale dataset comprising over one million meticulously curated editing pairs. Extensive experiments demonstrate that Audio-Omni achieves state-of-the-art performance across a suite of benchmarks, outperforming prior unified approaches while achieving performance on par with or superior to specialized expert models. Beyond its core capabilities, Audio-Omni exhibits remarkable inherited capabilities, including knowledge-augmented reasoning generation, in-context generation, and zero-shot cross-lingual control for audio generation, highlighting a promising direction toward universal generative audio intelligence. The code, model, and dataset will be publicly released on https://zeyuet.github.io/Audio-Omni.\", \"status\": \"unread\", \"compile_status\": \"compiled\", \"compiled_at\": \"2026-04-28T05:01:58.174687\"}", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "170932d9-8c61-431c-9daf-1c4f200ba0a6", "uuid": "eb2290df-afcf-4e87-af86-3d8c02d0f1e0", "timestamp": "2026-07-11T17:46:03.535Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "{\"arxiv_id\": \"2604.10708\", \"title\": \"Audio-Omni: Extending Multi-modal Understanding to Versatile Audio Generation and Editing\", \"authors\": [\"Zeyue Tian\", \"Binxin Yang\", \"Zhaoyang Liu\", \"Jiexuan Zhang\", \"Ruibin Yuan\", \"Hubery Yin\", \"Qifeng Chen\", \"Chen Li\", \"Jing Lv\", \"Wei Xue\", \"Yike Guo\"], \"year\": 2026, \"venue\": \"\", \"categories\": [\"cs.SD\", \"cs.AI\", \"cs.CV\", \"cs.MM\"], \"topic\": \"tts_vc\", \"tags\": [\"LALM\", \"LALM/\\u97f3\\u9891\\u6807\\u8bb0-\\u878d\\u5408\", \