{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a9ffda2f370e3bb2", "type": "tool_result", "content": "{\n  \"arxiv_id\": \"2605.18749\",\n  \"title\": \"WavFlow: Audio Generation in Waveform Space\",\n  \"authors\": [\n    \"Feiyan Zhou\",\n    \"Luyuan Wang\",\n    \"Shoufa Chen\",\n    \"Zhe Wang\",\n    \"Zhiheng Liu\",\n    \"Yuren Cong\",\n    \"Xiaohui Zhang\",\n    \"Fanny Yang\",\n    \"Belinda Zeng\"\n  ],\n  \"contributions\": [\n    \"WavFlow introduces a simplified architecture that synthesizes high-fidelity audio directly in raw waveform space using waveform patchify, x-prediction flow matching, and specialized signal preprocessing to eliminate the need for audio tokenizers.\",\n    \"An automated data curation pipeline is developed to harvest large-scale, high-quality video-text-audio triplets to address the sensitivity of direct waveform modeling to data quality and scale.\",\n    \"Empirical validation demonstrates competitive results on VGGSound and AudioCaps benchmarks, proving that end-to-end raw waveform generation matches or exceeds the performance of established latent-based methods.\"\n  ],\n  \"tags\": [\n    \"TTS\",\n    \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-NAR-Flow\"\n  ],\n  \"abstract\": \"Modern audio generation predominantly relies on latent-space compression, introducing additional complexity and potential information loss. In this work, we challenge this paradigm with WavFlow, a framework that generates high-fidelity audio directly in raw waveform space without intermediate representations. To overcome the inherent difficulties of modeling high-dimensional and low-energy signals, we reshape audio into 2D token grids through waveform patchify and introduce amplitude lifting to align signal scales, enabling stable optimization via direct x-prediction in flow matching. To capture complex semantic alignment and temporal synchronization, we leverage an automated data pipeline to curate 5 million high-quality video-text-audio triplets, allowing the model to learn fine-grained acoustic patterns from scratch. Experimental results show that WavFlow achieves competitive performance on the video-to-audio benchmark VGGSound (FD_PaSST: 59.98, IS_PANNs: 17.40, DeSync: 0.44) and the text-to-audio benchmark AudioCaps (FD_PANNs: 10.63, IS_PANNs: 12.62), matching or exceeding the performance of established latent-based methods. Our work demonstrates that intermediate compression is not a prerequisite for high-quality synthesis, offering a simpler and more scalable alternative for multimodal audio generation.\"\n}", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "170932d9-8c61-431c-9daf-1c4f200ba0a6", "uuid": "51483866-ca6f-4e72-a706-0c2977531974", "timestamp": "2026-07-11T17:46:19.352Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "{\n  \"arxiv_id\": \"2605.18749\",\n  \"title\": \"WavFlow: Audio Generation in Waveform Space\",\n  \"authors\": [\n    \"Feiyan Zhou\",\n    \"Luyuan Wang\",\n    \"Shoufa Chen\",\n    \"Zhe Wang\",\n    \"Zhiheng Liu\",\n    \"Yuren Cong\",\n    \"Xiaohui Zhang\",\n    \"Fanny Yang\",\n    \"Belinda Zeng\"\n  ],\n  \"contributions\": [\n    \"WavFlow introduces a simplified architecture that synthesizes high-fidelity audio directly in raw waveform space using waveform patchify, x-prediction flow matching, and specialized signal preprocessing to eliminate the need for audio tokenizers.\",\n    \"An automated data curation pipeline is developed to harvest large-scale, high-quality video-text-audio triplets to address the sensitivity of direct waveform modeling to data quality and scale.\",\n    \"Empirical validation demonstrates competitive results on VGGSound and AudioCaps benchmarks, proving that end-to-end raw waveform generation matches or exceeds the performance of established latent-based methods.\"\n  ],\n  \"tags\": [\n    \"TTS\",\n    \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-NAR-Flow\"\n  ],\n  \"abstract\": \"Modern audio generation predominantly relies on latent-space compression, introducing additional complexity and potential information loss. In this work, we challenge this paradigm with WavFlow, a framework that generates high-fidelity audio directly in raw waveform space without intermediate representations. To overcome the inherent difficulties of modeling high-dimensional and low-energy signals, we reshape audio into 2D token grids through waveform patchify and introduce amplitude lifting to align signal scales, enabling stable optimization via direct x-prediction in flow matching. To capture complex semantic alignment and temporal synchronization, we leverage an automated data pipeline to curate 5 million high-quality video-text-audio triplets, allowing the model to learn fine-grained acoustic patterns from scratch. Experimental results show that WavFlow achieves competitive performance on the video-to-audio benchmark VGGSound (FD_PaSST: 59.98, IS_PANNs: 17.40, DeSync: 0.44) and the text-to-audio benchmark AudioCaps (FD_PANNs: 10.63, IS_PANNs: 12.62), matching or exceeding the performance of established latent-based methods. Our work demonstrates that intermediate compression is not a prerequisite for high-quality synthesis, offering a simpler and more scalable alternative for multimodal audio generation.\"\n}", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
{"type": "assistant", "message": {"id": "msg_1783791991934", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "chatcmpl-tool-ac5b874ab287c024", "name": "Bash", "input": {"command": "uv run paper-wiki search -p 2410.06885 --format json 2>&1 | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps({k:d[k] for k in ['arxiv_id','title','authors','contributions','tags','abstract']}, indent=2))\" 2>&1 | head -40", "description": "Get details of V2A paper 2410.06885"}}], "model": "GLM-5.2-w4a8", "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 0, "output_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "170932d9-8c61-431c-9daf-1c4f200ba0a6", "uuid": "e6bdbe50-1c48-4abe-98a1-5bad67c07b6d"}
{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-ac5b874ab287c024", "type": "tool_result", "content": "{\n  \"arxiv_id\": \"2410.06885\",\n  \"title\": \"F5-TTS: A Fairytaler that Fakes Fluent and Faithful Speech with Flow Matching\",\n  \"authors\": [\n    \"Yushen Chen\",\n    \"Zhikang Niu\",\n    \"Ziyang Ma\",\n    \"Keqi Deng\",\n    \"Chunhui Wang\",\n    \"Jian Zhao\",\n    \"Kai Yu\",\n    \"Xie Chen\"\n  ],\n  \"contributions\": [\n    \"Introduces F5-TTS, a fully non-autoregressive text-to-speech system based on flow matching with a Diffusion Transformer (DiT) that eliminates the need for complex designs like duration models, text encoders, and phoneme alignment.\",\n    \"Improves text-speech alignment and model robustness by leveraging ConvNeXt V2 blocks to refine text representation before concatenation with speech features.\",\n    \"Proposes an inference-time Sway Sampling strategy for flow steps that significantly enhances generation performance and efficiency without requiring model retraining.\",\n    \"Achieves faster training and a highly efficient inference Real-Time Factor (RTF) of 0.15, outperforming existing state-of-the-art diffusion-based TTS models.\",\n    \"Demonstrates highly natural and expressive zero-shot ability, seamless code-switching capability, and speed control efficiency when trained on a public 100K hours multilingual dataset.\"\n  ],\n  \"tags\": [\n    \"TTS\",\n    \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-NAR-Flow\",\n    \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-DiT\",\n    \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u8bed\\u8a00\",\n    \"TTS/\\u63a7\\u5236-\\u53c2\\u8003\\u8bed\\u97f3\",\n    \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u5feb\\u901f\\u751f\\u6210\"\n  ],\n  \"abstract\": \"This paper introduces F5-TTS, a fully non-autoregressive text-to-speech system based on flow matching with Diffusion Transformer (DiT). Without requiring complex designs such as duration model, text encoder, and phoneme alignment, the text input is simply padded with filler tokens to the same length as input speech, and then the denoising is performed for speech generation, which was originally proved feasible by E2 TTS. However, the original design of E2 TTS makes it hard to follow due to its slow convergence and low robustness. To address these issues, we first model the input with ConvNeXt to refine the text representation, making it easy to align with the speech. We further propose an inference-time Sway Sampling strategy, which significantly improves our model's performance and efficiency. This sampling strategy for flow step can be easily applied to existing flow matching based models without retraining. Our design allows faster training and achieves an inference RTF of 0.15, which is greatly improved compared to state-of-the-art diffusion-based TTS models. Trained on a public 100K hours multilingual dataset, our F5-TTS exhibits highly natural and expressive zero-shot ability, seamless code-switching capability, and speed control efficiency. We have released all codes and checkpoints to promote community development, at https://SWivid.github.io/F5-TTS/.\"\n}", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "170932d9-8c61-431c-9daf-1c4f200ba0a6", "uuid": "f42d0e0b-80de-4b2e-b973-28880bcf66b2", "timestamp": "2026-07-11T17:46:34.496Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "{\n  \"arxiv_id\": \"2410.06885\",\n  \"title\": \"F5-TTS: A Fairytaler that Fakes Fluent and Faithful Speech with Flow Matching\",\n  \"authors\": [\n    \"Yushen Chen\",\n    \"Zhikang Niu\",\n    \"Ziyang Ma\",\n    \"Keqi Deng\",\n    \"Chunhui Wang\",\n    \"Jian Zhao\",\n    \"Kai Yu\",\n    \"Xie Chen\"\n  ],\n  \"contributions\": [\n    \"Introduces F5-TTS, a fully non-autoregressive text-to-speech system based on flow matching with a Diffusion Transformer (DiT) that eliminates the need for complex designs like duration models, text encoders, and phoneme alignment.\",\n    \"Improves text-speech alignment and model robustness by leveraging ConvNeXt V2 blocks to refine text representation before concatenation with speech features.\",\n    \"Proposes an inference-time Sway Sampling strategy for flow steps that significantly enhances generation performance and efficiency without requiring model retraining.\",\n    \"Achieves faster training and a highly efficient inference Real-Time Factor (RTF) of 0.15, outperforming existing state-of-the-art diffusion-based TTS models.\",\n    \"Demonstrates highly natural and expressive zero-shot ability, seamless code-switching capability, and speed control efficiency when trained on a public 100K hours multilingual dataset.\"\n  ],\n  \"tags\": [\n    \"TTS\",\n    \"TTS/\\u67b6\\u6784-NAR-Flow\",\n    \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-DiT\",\n    \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u591a\\u8bed\\u8a00\",\n    \"TTS/\\u63a7\\u5236-\\u53c2\\u8003\\u8bed\\u97f3\",\n    \"TTS/\\u529f\\u80fd-\\u5feb\\u901f\\u751f\\u6210\"\n  ],\n  \"abstract\": \"This paper introduces F5-TTS, a fully non-autoregressive text-to-speech system based on flow matching with Diffusion Transformer (DiT). Without requiring complex designs such as duration model, text encoder, and phoneme alignment, the text input is simply padded with filler tokens to the same length as input speech, and then the denoising is performed for speech generation, which was originally proved feasible by E2 TTS. However, the original design of E2 TTS makes it hard to follow due to its slow convergence and low robustness. To address these issues, we first model the input with ConvNeXt to refine the text representation, making it easy to align with the speech. We further propose an inference-time Sway Sampling strategy, which significantly improves our model's performance and efficiency. This sampling strategy for flow step can be easily applied to existing flow matching based models without retraining. Our design allows faster training and achieves an inference RTF of 0.15, which is greatly improved compared to state-of-the-art diffusion-based TTS models. Trained on a public 100K hours multilingual dataset, our F5-TTS exhibits highly natural and expressive zero-shot ability, seamless code-switching capability, and speed control efficiency. We have released all codes and checkpoints to promote community development, at https://SWivid.github.io/F5-TTS/.\"\n}", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
